commentTextItems.html: leans forward and drives it exquisitely wide of mid off to get the winning runs

commentPostTextItems.html: Dravid does it for India this time while chasing
Indians have maintained their cool under pressure
Everyone contributed with the bat for India except for Laxman
But it was SURELY Sehwag who made all the difference
India sending warning signals to Sri Lanka!
Jayasuriya and CO. should be hoping that India don't continue their run of consistency
Join us on Sunday 5th August for the final, Sri Lanka v India. India have beaten Sri Lanka twice so far. It definitely promises to be  a cracker of a game, cliched as it may seem
Its a day/night game, starts at 0830 GMT (1430 Sri Lanka time). So Join us on CricInfo.com
Meanwhile you can check out http://www.cricinfo.com/link_to_database/ARCHIVE/2001/OD_TOURNEYS/CCC-SL for writeups, columns, features, contests, audio interviews etc. related to this tournmament

commentTextItems.html: leans well forward and drives it to long on with ease to reach his 50
pushes it past the bowler's foot to long on for the single
short ball, picks it amazingly well over mid wicket, excellent shot from the youngster
comes down the track and pushes it to long on for the easy single to keep strike

commentPostTextItems.html: McMillam comes back witrh the ball

stories.title: 9th Match, India v New Zealand, Coca Cola Cup, Statistical Highlights
stories.summary: It was the 1743rd ODI in cricket history

stories.title: Just one guy took it away from us: Fleming
stories.summary: New Zealand captain Stephen Fleming, speaking after India defeated his side to qualify for the final of the Coca-Cola Cup, paid tribute to Virender Shewag who took the game away from them with a sparkling 100 off just 69 deliveries, the seventh

stories.title: I just played my natural game, says Shewag
stories.summary:
Asked to open the innings in the absence of batting maestro Sachin
Tendulkar, 22-year-old Virender Shewag could not have chosen a better
occasion to live up to his reputation as a hard-hitting batsman

stories.title: Shewag ton powers India to title clash with Sri Lanka
stories.summary:
Looking down and out after their first three games, India stormed into
the final of the Coca-Cola Cup at a sun bathed Sinhalese Sports Club
today after their best batting performance of the tournament to
date

stories.title: Shewag's century not enough for place in Test squad
stories.summary:
A brilliant maiden 100 by all-rounder Virender Shewag in the crucial
one-day league match of the Coca-Cola Cup tri-series against New
Zealand, was not enough to earn him a place in the Test squad
announced by the selectors in Mumbai today
